# Ingredients

Serves 2

- 1 tbsp oil
- 1/2 onion
- 10g ginger
- 2 garlic cloves
- lemon
- 1 can chick peas
- 1/2 tsp fennel seeds
- 1 tbsp curry powder
- 3 tomatoes, chopped, or passata
- 3 dates
- yougurt
- coriander

# Instructions

1. Heat the oil and cook the onion, ginger and garlic for 5 minutes
2. Peel 2 strips of lemon and add to the pan along with the chick peas and fennel seeds. Cook for 5 minutes
3. Sitr in the curry, tomatoes and dates, cook for 5 minutes
4. Add 50-100ml of water (depending on the tomatoes used) and continue to simmer for 5-10 minutes, until thickened
5. Switch off the stove, squeeze in a little lemon juice and season to taste
6. Serve with a paratha, yougurt and coriander

